    "body": "[https://book.getfoundry.sh/cast/index.html](https://book.getfoundry.sh/cast/index.html) shows a very similar example.\r\n\r\ncast:\r\n`cast call 0x6b175474e89094c44da98b954eedeac495271d0f \"balanceOf()(address)\" --rpc-url https://eth-mainnet.alchemyapi.io/v2/<apikey>`\r\n\r\nif you want to use it in a forge test, you can use `--fork-url` ([see here](https://book.getfoundry.sh/forge/forking-mode.html?highlight=fork#forking-mode)). In your test, import the balanceOf function in an interface, and call it in your test to the address of your token.\r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\ninterface IERC20 {\r\n  function balanceOf(address) external view returns (uint256);\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract getBalance {\r\n  ...\r\n  \r\n  function fetchBalance(address tokenAddress, address holder) public view returns (uint256 balance) {\r\n    balance = IERC20(tokenAddress).balanceOf(holder);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n",
